Engagement editorials pt 1.

We have quietly celebrated our engagement, only sharing with family, for the last few weeks. Tony proposed at the Lincoln memorial late in the evening, just the two of us, while a kind dog walker happened to be at the bottom of the steps and snapped the moment (swipe to the end to see). 

My parents captured our engagement photos (dad is my second photographer for weddings @kathleenmariephoto). 

Our love is quiet, relaxed, intimate and overflowing. It is laughter, tears and gentle promises of “I’ve got you” when the world’s stresses are overwhelming. It is the fruition of my patient endurance of faith. 

We are overjoyed to share this new season. Pt 2 will be up shortly.

Bucket list item checked off: visit the NYC @polene_paris store!

After lunch Tony took me to this gorgeous shop to pick out my second Polène bag. I knew I wanted the moon shaped Numèro Dix but I wasn’t sure which color. I already own the Numèro Neuf in chalk so it was a difficult decision as I love neutrals. 

The sales consultant was amazing and brought out every color of Dix so I could best choose. I had narrowed it down to the textured camel and textured black. 

After quite a bit of time deciding, we felt the textured camel would be the best color for me. 

Next, I picked out a keychain crafted from leftover leather to personalize with my initials. 

It was a huge highlight of our trip and I hope I can visit this beautiful shop again! 🤎

A weekend getaway from Washington, DC to NYC with @thejet.coach 

I love traveling, but long car rides aren’t my favorite. When we found the Jet Coach and it’s motion cancelling seat technology, I had to give it a try. The seats move with the coach to eliminate 90% of bumps and vibration, making the 4hr car ride to NYC super comfortable!

Aside from the motion cancelling seats, I really appreciated having gluten free snack options for the ride. 

@thejet.coach is my favorite way to visit NYC! Tony and I are already planning our next trip 🗽

“The Liberty of Color,” a vibrant installation by beloved local artist Maggie O’Neill that has transformed the Bourbon Steak Patio into a vivid oasis this summer. 

“The Liberty of Color” installation showcases every hue of the rainbow, celebrating individuality and diversity with two 8 feet tall, hand-painted Lady Liberty statues, suspended disco balls and a large drip flag. O’Neill’s work invites guests to “Pledge Allegiance to Color,” symbolizing unity, while creating an inclusive and colorful home for an ongoing summer series.

Starting June 25th, guests can enjoy this colorful installation as well as a live dj!

The absolute best part of the evening was having the opportunity with my sister to paint with @maggieoartist 🌈

Date night in Washington, DC: visit the brand new summer installation “Look Here” 

This year’s immersive installation, LOOK HERE, uses mirrors shaped like origami fortune tellers, nine-foot-tall kaleidoscopes, and images of historic activist marches, inviting visitors to envision themselves as part of DC’s most significant moments.

The exhibition was designed by architect Suchi Reddy of Reddymade Architecture and Design. @reddymadedesign “As visitors experience these powerful images of activism in LOOK HERE, it’s my hope they will see themselves in the reflective surfaces as part of these important moments in our collective history.”

The exhibit was truly gorgeous to experience, with the sunlight bouncing off each mirror with a piece of history. The museum is hosting several summer events featuring food, drinks + dancing, which will be the perfect atmosphere to experience the installation!

Partners for life.

The thing is—I’ve been collecting vintage Barbies for the last 22 years. Barbie was a huge role model for me growing up; from her regal and luxe aesthetic to her limitless talents, I wanted to be strong and beautiful like Barbie.

While I did play with my 90s Barbie’s growing up, my vintage (1960s-late 1970s) Barbie collecting began when I was 10 wondering through an antique shop and saw her: the original Barbie. From that point on my collection grew. I started photographing my Barbies that same year, creating stories with my Barbies, longing to be a photographer for Mattel.

While that dream didn’t happen, I did become an award winning wedding photographer and I have Barbie to thank for my photography inspiration. 

The @barbiethemovie was everything I hoped it would be; I loved the history and subtle jokes included in the movie true @barbie collectors + lovers would appreciate.

The best part for me was seeing Allan—Ken’s best friend—a ginger haired stud only produced from 1964-1966. He was, in my opinion, a sweeter version than Ken. I remember finding a 1964 Allan in an antique shop when I was 15 and promptly scooped him up. It took about 10 years to organically find his girlfriend Midge in a shop but now the two are together on my doll shelf.

I brought my Enchanted Evening Barbie with me to the premiere last night and absolutely loved every second of the movie.

Pi·la·tes 🤸🏼‍♀️

2020 threw me into a health journey filled with mystery, medications, doctor visits and learning how to give my body grace. 

Pilates has been a beautiful part of my journey. I’ve grown confidence in strengthening my balance, coordination and performing exercises I never thought I could. 

It takes an unwavering amount of persistence to get myself out of the bed everyday and when I can, I attend a Pilates class to keep loving my body through these classes.

*Invisible health conditions can be lonely, frightening and discouraging. Please know the journey will improve and you are loved. There are so many in person and online support groups and communities to help 🩶

A question I’m often asked is: do I need to wear gluten free makeup?

Makeup containing gluten can’t penetrate the skin, but if a lipstick is made with gluten and I ingest it throughout the day then I’m essentially consuming gluten. It gives me a peace of mind limiting my exposure to gluten while I learn how sensitive I am and how best to heal my body. 

Hourglass has a whole page on their website dedicated to products that are gluten free. Charlotte Tilbury launched their latest lipsticks without gluten. Tarte has gorgeous lip liners and most of their products are gluten free.

At the end of the day I’d rather be safe than regret gluten exposure ✌🏻

I created the perfect lipstick for my wedding day! 💍

I visited @liplab to design and fully customize the lipstick I’ll wear when I say “I do.” At Lip Lab I designed the lipstick finish (matte, satin or sheer), the flavor (mint, rose, vanilla), the color, tube shade and engraved my tube! It was a truly special experience seeing the Color Expert mix shades that matched my vision for the lipstick as well which tones would complement my complexion. 

It was very important to find a lipstick that was gluten free and I was shocked when I learned Lip Lab products were not only gluten free but cruelty-free, vegan, paraben-free and talc-free!

Lip Lab offers limited edition sugar cookie, pomegranate, and mango flavors as well as custom Gloss and Butter Balm Services! 

Their new location has opened at the Wharf in Washington, DC. I might not be able to wait until my wedding day to wear this special lipstick so I’ll have to pop back in for a refill 😂 Refills are easy to do online too under the re-order tab on their website.
